{
"hypothesis": "Objects in the grid are duplicated vertically based on their initial position from the top to the bottom of the grid. Each object is replicated based on the number of its initial vertical position plus one.",
"sub_hypotheses": [
"Level 1: Each individual object is duplicated vertically. The number of duplicates is the same as the object's initial vertical position plus one.",
"Level 2: All objects maintain their original relative horizontal positions during duplication. The vertical position of the duplicates is determined by the original position of the object.",
"Level 3: The overall grid expands vertically, having more rows as a result of the vertical duplication of objects. The grid maintains its original width."]
}
